d","content_id":"35ec21d9-c787-4821-871c-f914069e7904","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Sellafield Ltd","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Sellafield Ltd","image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/organisation/logo/1220/Sellafield_Ltd_logo.jpg","alt_text":"Sellafield Ltd"}},"brand":"department-for-business-innovation-skills","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/231/s300_SL_logo_image_3_.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/231/s960_SL_logo_image_3_.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/sellafield-ltd","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/sellafield-ltd"}],"primary_publishing_organisation":[{"analytics_identifier":"PB197","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority","base_path":"/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority","content_id":"bd692b3d-2d4c-43d9-aa85-32c465e1984a","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Nuclear Decommissioning Authority","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Nuclear \u003cbr/\u003eDecommissioning \u003cbr/\u003eAuthority","image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/organisation/logo/197/NDA_final_logo_Black185.jpg","alt_text":"Nuclear Decommissioning Authority"}},"brand":"department-for-business-innovation-skills","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/184/s300_news_article960x640.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/184/s960_news_article960x640.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Nuclear employees WiN big at national diversity conference","public_updated_at":"2019-02-07T15:04:15Z","document_type":"news_story","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/nuclear-employees-win-big-at-national-diversity-conference","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/nuclear-employees-win-big-at-national-diversity-conference","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"8badd242-140f-4417-931f-fcb63be8bfeb","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/nuclear-employees-win-big-at-national-diversity-conference","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/nuclear-employees-win-big-at-national-diversity-conference","links":{}}]},"description":"Employees from across the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) group were honoured at a national awards ceremony for their work in addressing gender imbalance and diversity in the nuclear industry.","details":{"body":"\u003cp\u003ePhil Craig, former Managing Director of Dounreay, scooped the coveted ‘Ally of the Year’ title at the Women in Nuclear (\u003cabbr title=\"Women in Nuclear\"\u003eWiN\u003c/abbr\u003e) UK conference yesterday, for being a leading male advocate of gender balance and diversity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePhil said it was an honour to have been recognised for putting people at the centre of the business:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003eI’m incredibly proud of all of the work that has been undertaken at Dounreay during my time there, specifically in relation to equality, diversity and inclusion.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003cp\u003eAll of this work, and the reason for this nomination, is because of the effort and commitment of the site staff, who are committed to delivering the mission but also to making a difference in the  people agenda.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003cp class=\"last-child\"\u003eTo have been part of that journey and to be recognised by them, is the most humbling part of all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGayle Rew, Chair of Magnox Women’s Network, scooped the ‘Mission Possible’ award for her help in building vital networks. Gayle said:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    \u003cp class=\"last-child\"\u003eI am absolutely thrilled to have won the award and to gain the recognition for the progress that we have made in Magnox with our Women’s Network.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n  \u003cp\u003eI am incredibly proud of what we have achieved since our first tentative steps two years ago, including hosting our own conference, raising awareness of the need for gender balance and growing our membership.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003cp class=\"last-child\"\u003eThe \u003cabbr title=\"Women in Nuclear\"\u003eWiN\u003c/abbr\u003e conference has been a great opportunity to meet with so many like-minded and inspirational people who are also working hard across our sector to improve gender balance and inclusion.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis year’s conference, held in London, focused on conscious inclusion. It saw workshop sessions and panel discussions including one with Anne Jenkins, Head of Equality, Diversity and Inclusion at the NDA, and Nikos Adamidis from NDA, who picked up last year’s inaugural ‘Ally of the Year’ prize.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnne said:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cabbr title=\"Women in Nuclear\"\u003eWiN\u003c/abbr\u003e members have worked hard to help build a culture of inclusion within the industry and the awards are testament to the passion and commitment of everyone involved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003cp\u003eThis year’s conference theme of conscious inclusion highlights the importance of understanding that organisational culture plays a crucial part in attracting, developing and retaining talent.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003cp class=\"last-child\"\u003eProgress is being made, however, sustained culture change takes time and there’s still a long way to go, but \u003cabbr title=\"Women in Nuclear\"\u003eWiN\u003c/abbr\u003e have once again shown their passion and energy to support the industry in its ambitions to be an inclusive place to work.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCurrently only 22% of the UK’s nuclear industry is female, and this number declines significantly at senior levels. There is strong evidence to suggest that an inclusive environment, with diverse teams, leads to better performance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eEmployees from across the NDA group were shortlisted in the award categories including Sellafield’s Stephen Bewsher and Radioactive Waste Management’s (\u003cabbr title=\"Radioactive Waste Management\"\u003eRWM\u003c/abbr\u003e) Liam Payne, for ‘Ally of the Year’, and Samantha King, of \u003cabbr title=\"Radioactive Waste Management\"\u003eRWM\u003c/abbr\u003e, for ‘Mission Possible’.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePrioritising diversity and inclusion issues has been a major focus within the NDA group over past year in a bid to future-proof the business by attracting and retaining the right people with the right skills.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c5c484ced915d041f3a8af1/gayle-rew-960-x-640.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5c5c484b40f0b676c66a25fa/gayle-rew-960-x-640.jpg","alt_text":"Gayle Rew, Chair of Magnox Women's Network, wins the \"Mission Possible\" Award 2019.","caption":"Gayle Rew, Chair of Magnox Women's Network, wins the \"Mission Possible\" Award 2019.","credit":"Magnox Ltd"},"change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-01-31T14:36:25.112Z"},{"note":"Added new photo of Gayle Rew.","public_timestamp":"2019-02-07T15:04:04.860Z"}]}}